media.headline: Eaton's solo homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Eaton hits first home run with the Nationals
media.bigblurb: Adam Eaton gets the Nationals on the board with a solo home run, his first as a member of the team, giving the Nats a 1-0 lead in the 1st

media.headline: Harper's 'look away' catch
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Harper fights sun, tumbles for great catch
media.bigblurb: Bryce Harper fights the sun on J.T. Realmuto's liner, but sticks out his glove at the last second and tumbles for an outstanding catch

media.headline: Koehler gets DP, escapes trouble
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Koehler induces DP, escapes jam in 3rd
media.bigblurb: Tom Koehler gets Ryan Zimmerman to ground into a 6-4-3 double play with two runners on, ending the 3rd inning

media.headline: Stanton carries shattered bat
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Stanton breaks bat, runs with piece to first
media.bigblurb: Giancarlo Stanton shatters his bat on a check-swing grounder to short and carries the remaining shard to first as he runs it out

media.headline: Fan makes great catch with hat
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Fan snags a foul ball with his hat
media.bigblurb: An alert fan grabs the hat from his head and sticks it out to make an outstanding catch on Christian Yelich's foul ball

media.headline: Rain delays game in the 6th
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Marlins, Nats delayed by rain in the 6th
media.bigblurb: The Marlins-Nationals game gets delayed by rain for the second time in the bottom of the 6th inning

media.headline: Werth's over-the-shoulder catch
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Werth races back for over-the-shoulder catch
media.bigblurb: Jayson Werth runs toward the left-center-field gap on Dee Gordon's deep fly ball and makes an over-the-shoulder catch with two hands

media.headline: Werth's solo homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Werth doubles lead with a solo shot
media.bigblurb: Jayson Werth increases the Nationals' lead to 2-0 in the bottom of the 7th inning with a solo home run over the left-field wall

media.headline: Must C: Harper's no-look catch
media.blurb: Must C Catch: Harper battles sun, makes a great grab
media.bigblurb: Bryce Harper hustles to his right and fights through the sun, then sticks out his glove to make a slick no-look catch in right field

media.headline: Gonzalez's scoreless start
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Gonzalez fans seven in six scoreless innings
media.bigblurb: Gio Gonzalez keeps the Marlins off the board in his six scoreless innings of work, allowing seven hits and walking one while fanning seven

media.headline: Realmuto's game-tying homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Realmuto ties it up with a two-run shot
media.bigblurb: J.T. Realmuto ties the game at 2 with one swing, launching a two-run home run over the center-field wall in the top of the 8th inning

media.headline: Zimmerman's go-ahead homer
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Zimmerman gets homer after call overturned
media.bigblurb: The umpires review Ryan Zimmerman's deep fly ball above the center-field wall and the call is overturned, giving him a home run in the 8th

media.headline: Murphy starts DP in the 9th
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Murphy nets DP, call confirmed in the 9th
media.bigblurb: Daniel Murphy starts a 4-6-3 double play in the top of the 9th inning, and after the Marlins challenge, the call is confirmed

media.headline: Moore's game-tying single
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Moore ties game with an RBI single
media.bigblurb: Tyler Moore ties the game in the top of the 9th inning with an RBI single up the middle that scores Adeiny Hechavarria

media.headline: Bour's unassisted DP in the 9th
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Bour sends it to extras with unassisted DP
media.bigblurb: Justin Bour snags Trea Turner's liner and steps on first for an unassisted double play, sending the game to extra innings

media.headline: Bour's go-ahead RBI double
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Bour puts Marlins ahead with RBI double
media.bigblurb: Justin Bour puts the Marlins ahead in the top of the 10th with an RBI double down the left-field line that scores J.T. Realmuto from first

media.headline: Ramos earns save in extras
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Ramos notches first save of the season
media.bigblurb: A.J. Ramos gets Anthony Rendon to pop up for the final out, earning his first save of the season in the Marlins' 4-3 win in extra innings

media.headline: Gonzalez nabs Gordon at first
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Gonzalez throws out Gordon on a bunt attempt
media.bigblurb: Gio Gonzalez hustles off the mound to field Dee Gordon's bunt attempt and throws him out to start off the top of the 1st inning

media.headline: Zimmerman homers after review
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Zimmerman gets homer after call overturned
media.bigblurb: Ryan Zimmerman puts the Nationals ahead with a solo home run after the umpires review and overturn the triple call in the 8th

media.headline: Treinen freezes Yelich
media.blurb: MIA@WAS: Treinen strikes out Yelich in the 9th
media.bigblurb: Blake Treinen catches Christian Yelich looking at a called strike three, ending the top of the 9th inning

media.headline: Baker on loss to Miami
media.blurb: MIA@WSH: Baker on extra-inning loss to the Marlins
media.bigblurb: Nationals manager Dusty Baker discusses Gio Gonzalez's scoreless outing and the effort in the extra-inning loss to the Marlins

media.headline: Mattingly on 4-3 win in extras
media.blurb: MIA@WAS: Mattingly on comeback victory in 10 innings
media.bigblurb: Marlins manager Don Mattingly discusses Justin Bour's go-ahead double in the 10th and J.T. Realmuto's offense in extra-innings comeback win

media.headline: 4/6/17 CG: MIA@WSH
media.blurb: 4/6/17 Condensed Game: MIA@WSH
media.bigblurb: 4/6/17 Condensed Game: MIA@WSH

media.headline: Recap: MIA 4, WSH 3 - F/10
media.blurb: 4/6/17: Bour's go-ahead double in 10th lifts Marlins
media.bigblurb: Daily Recap: Justin Bour hit the go-ahead RBI double in the top of the 10th and A.J. Ramos locked down the save in the Marlins' 4-3 win
